<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="count-v">count <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /kaʊnt/    美 /kaʊnt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>数数：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>count from</strong> one <strong>to</strong> one thousand 
从1数到1000</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>count</strong> ( <strong>up</strong> ) <strong>to</strong> ten
数到10</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>计算总数：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There are 12 weeks to go, <strong>counting from</strong> today.
从今天算起还有12个星期。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— How much money have you got exactly?
你到底挣了多少钱？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Well, I’ve got no time to count it.
哎，我还没时间算呢。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>把...计算在内；包括</strong></h4>
<p>to include sb / sth in a total：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There are more than 380 of us on the plane, <strong>not counting</strong> the crew.
不算机组人员，飞机上有380多人。</p></div>

<h4 id="4-matter">4.★ <strong>[不用于进行时] 重要(matter)；有价值</strong></h4>
<p>to be important or valuable:</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>First impressions really do count.
第一印象真的很重要。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’ve always believed that happiness counts more than money.
我一直认为幸福比金钱更重要。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It is</strong> not how much you read but what you read <strong>that counts</strong>.
重要的不是你读了多少，而是你读了什么。</p><footer>2009 浙江</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His promises <strong>count for</strong> nothing.
他的承诺一点价值也没有。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.<strong>看作；认为</strong></h4>
<p>to consider：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I <strong>count myself lucky</strong> to have a job.
我有工作，实在很幸运。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I <strong>count</strong> her <strong>as</strong> one of my best friends.
我把她视为我最好的一个朋友。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="count-on-upon">count on / upon</h3>
<p>1.<strong>依靠；依赖；指望</strong><br />
 to depend on sb or sth, especially in a difficult situation：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>That was the first time Dad had counted on me in a moment of emergency.
这是父亲第一次在危急时刻依赖我。</p><footer>2011 重庆</footer></div>

<h3 id="count-down">count down</h3>
<p>1.<strong>(某一特殊时刻之前) 倒计时；倒数：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She has been counting down to the big day. 
她已经在对这个重大的日子倒计时了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>countable /'kaʊntəbl/ adj <br />
countless /'kaʊntləs/ adj   </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My mother and I conflicted <strong>countless times</strong> over the years.
这些年来我和母亲发生了无数次冲突。</p><footer>2014 江苏</footer></div>

<h2 id="_4">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The whole team count <strong><em>_</em></strong> Cristiano Ronaldo, and he seldom lets them down.  （2015 江苏改）  </li>
<li>Surely it doesn’t matter where the student associations get their money from; what <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (count) is what they do with it.  （2007 湖北改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. on / upon  2. counts  </p></div>